text:
what will happen when we think about what is right with people rather than fixating on what is wrong with them?
—————— 🎙 ——————
dieses zitat von donald e. clifton, dem begründer der stärken-psychologie inspirierte mich vor knapp einem jahr dazu ein neues projekt zu starten: mein erstes buch.
.
als führungskraft und manager war mir vom ersten tag an eine sache wichtiger als alles andere: die stärken meiner mitarbeiter zu erkennen, zu fördern und einzusetzen. .
jeder mensch hat seinen u.s.p.: sein unique strength potential - also die eine fähigkeit in der sie das potenzial hat überdurchschnittliches zu leisten. diese fähigkeit gilt es zu erkennen, sie zur superkraft auszubauen und die menschen ständig in situationen zu bringen wo sie diese ausleben können.
.
nach einem jahr arbeit habe ich gestern #feierdichselbst released - mein buch, in dem ich den fahrplan offenlege, wie jeder mensch es schaffen kann seinen usp zu finden und auszuleben... bei sich selbst und anderen.
. 
das resultat dieses prozesses? ein unerschütterlicher glaube an seine eigene person. ein glaube, der dich selbstbewusster, überzeugender und selbstsicherer machen wird. .
ich hoffe das buch macht jedem freude, der es liest und legt den grundstein für ein erfolgreiches jahr 2019 für jeden von euch!
.
nur wenn wir aufhören menschen danach zu beurteilen, was sie nicht können und anfangen sie zu feiern, für das, was sie wirklich gut machen, werden wir das volle potenzial entfachen was in jedem steckt. 🔥
. 
danke an alle die mich auf diesem weg unterstützt haben! special thanks gehen an @schahnam für die grafische umsetzung und @flomoshammer für das cover pic! .
🥂 cheers to a happy new year full of ignited potentials! #pedramparsaian #pedramsays #feierdichselbst #team168

jeder mensch hat seinen u.s.p.: sein unique strength potential - also die eine fähigkeit in der sie das potenzial hat überdurchschnittliches zu leisten. diese fähigkeit gilt es zu erkennen, sie zur superkraft auszubauen und die menschen ständig in situationen zu bringen wo sie diese ausleben können.
.
nach einem jahr arbeit habe ich gestern  released - mein buch, in dem ich den fahrplan offenlege, wie jeder mensch es schaffen kann seinen usp zu finden und auszuleben... bei sich selbst und anderen.
. 
das resultat dieses prozesses? ein unerschütterlicher glaube an seine eigene person. ein glaube, der dich selbstbewusster, überzeugender und selbstsicherer machen wird. .
ich hoffe das buch macht jedem freude, der es liest und legt den grundstein für ein erfolgreiches jahr 2019 für jeden von euch!
.
nur wenn wir aufhören menschen danach zu beueilen, was sie nicht können und anfangen sie zu feiern, für das, was sie wirklich gut machen, werden wir das volle potenzial entfachen was in jedem steckt. 🔥
. 
danke an alle die mich auf diesem weg unterstützt haben! special thanks gehen an  für die grafische umsetzung und  für das cover pic! .
🥂 cheers to a happy new year full of ignited potentials!

text:
my heart is full 💗christmas came early for us this year. 
the boys & i spent the last few weeks in boston with my beautifully glowing daughter in anticipation of our newest addition #zyllahlondon who blessed us with an early arrival on dec 9th.  congratulations mariah & rick!! a perfect healthy 9lbs, 12oz baby girl, precious in every way.  i am completely & totally proud of my daughters unwavering strength.  9 months of planning for a lifetime of love! it was an honor to be a part of such a beautiful experience, filled with so many emotions. it was so so hard leaving my east coast fam. beyond grateful for the time we spent together & for ft so we can always be close. we returned home christmas eve to a warm, cozy, thoughtfully planned out welcome from our amazing santa.  it felt good to be home, couldn’t have been more perfect!! family is the best part of our holidays. may this season warm your soul, fill your heart with overflowing love and bless you with everything this life has to offer.  merry christmas 🎀🥰🎄🌟♥️🙏🏽

text:
i know there is a genuine confusion and awkwardness about how to approach someone you like.
it's because nobody talks to us about these things.
but keep these things in mind
1) don't always expect a response.
2) the person isn't entitled to talk to you. respect that boundary.
3)if they're interested, they'll respond.read the body language
4) if they're closed and reserved, try and stop the conversation. they're probably getting freaked out
5) if you're complimenting, choose your words carefully.

you don't know anyone's past and why they might be scared or reserved. 
you don't know how new people preceive you. be careful

so, you and your partner(s) are at the stage in your relationship where you want to get physically intimate.
or you're at a club where the wine is flowing, music is pounding, eyes match,  chemistry is in the air and you're about to get lucky!

but you know that voice in your head that's wondering if it's safe? listen to it! this is an idiot proof guide to make sure you don't walk away from the bed with more than just passionate memories.

step 1 is consent. in this age, it's extremely important to make sure that everyone involved agrees to have sex. no means no! 
be clear in what you are proposing. nothing is sexier than standing for your conviction and being confident.
be safe, be sober, be clear!

check out our other posts for steps 2 and 3 for the rest of the guide 
thanks as well to @doc.shail for helping compile this guide.

text:
существуют ли знаки судьбы?🤔
⠀
появление в нашей жизни тех или иных людей👫 можно отнести к знакам судьбы.
⠀
например, вы задумываете 🤔 какое- то дело, но боитесь, что у вас ничего не получится🙄.вам сложно решиться сделать первый шаг, вы сомневаетесь☹, в вас борются мечта🏝 и боязнь нарушить привычное течение жизни🏞.
⠀
и вот😊, если вам на самом деле суждено взяться за это дело🤗, довести его до конца, то рядом с вами обязательно появится человек💁‍♂️, который своими действиями, своими словами😊или своим примером толкает вас к тому самому первому📈 шагу!
⠀
в моей жизни такой человек 😊появился, мое отношение к жизни начало меняться и я рада таким переменам в жизни!🤗
⠀
знаки судьбы повсюду, они не оставляют нас без своего покровительства😇, без своих подсказок.
⠀
надо только уметь их слышать и к ним прислушиваться и тогда все встанет на свои места!⌛
⠀

text:
using this yummy olive oil today! was a gift from my management team, i am sure everyone else on my team got wine. i used to get wine as well, often times as a gift for winning a contest or something like that and often around the holidays. 
it was hard to be honest about it in the beginning but now it's not an issue and they know i prefer fancy olive oil and have made sure our events have non alcoholic beer for me 💓 honesty has been the only way for me to succeed while staying sober 
don't believe the narrative that recovery is painful and impossible to accomplish in corporate america. there are so many people who told me my career would be over and i would not be able to maintain long term sobriety in technology sales and it's simply not true.  it's so crazy to me now that i felt the same way, i thought it was impossible for years. but i got help for myself and implemented my sobriety while continuing my challenging career because of the lessons i learned in treatment. i didn't try to do it on my own because i don't believe in that approach about anything in life. i get help from professionals in all areas of my life and why would sobriety be any different? i went to aa in the beginning but felt like it was just incredibly ineffective for the time commitment and didn't provide much in terms of wellness. i need more than just a support group.  i needed individual treatment and my insurance benefits covered holistic treatment so there was no reason not to use the coverage i am entitled to. it was only after arriving in rehab that i learned how rare i was... only 8 percent of employers even have anyone using their benefits for recovery 😥 the stigma attached to addiction is so strong we hide and it gets worse. 
treatment is more effective when it's given earlier in the progression of the issue. don't let the stigma stop you from living your best life! 
#godry #drydiet #sober #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #mentalhealth #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #mentalhealth #nohangover #noalcohol #oliveoil

text:
what is trauma-focused therapy? this is also known as trauma-informed care (tic). tic is not about specific therapeutic techniques.  it is an overall approach, a philosophy of providing care. 
addresses the specific emotional and mental health needs of those who are struggling to overcome the effects of traumatic experiences. 
key principles of tic: 
1.a safe therapeutic environment is essential to aid in recovery. 
2.trauma-related symptoms and behaviors originate from adapting to traumatic experiences. 
3. recovery from trauma is identified as a goal in treatment. 
4. resiliency and trauma-resistant skills training are part of treatment. 
5. trauma-informed care includes a focus on strengths rather than pathology. 
6. trauma recovery is a collaborative effort between therapist and client
.

text:
a little boy sexually molested for several years. life repeatedly showed and reaffirmed he wasn’t wanted or loved by anyone even through adulthood. no one would listen. what wouldn’t we do for love, to feel we belonged and wanted?  what wouldn’t we do to stop the pain? how do you feel about this little boy?  too often he held a cold black steel muzzle of a gun on the temple or mouth, told lies, deceptions, infidelities, stuff unfathomable. [. ]
how would you feel if the little boy found love, attention, and all the worlds blessings and is now living his purpose, freely, happily, and with all the love he could ever want and also chooses to share his secrets of a turned around life with anyone who would listen.
[. ]
would you listen?  would you want to know more?
[. ]
by the way, the little boy was me, the new man is also me. perfectly imperfect.
[. ]

as promised, here are some of the benefits of aloe vera juice:👎👎👎👎👎
.
.
.
aloe vera contains proteolytic enzymes, which help heal and repair the damaged cells in your scalp. this improves the health of the hair follicles and indirectly boosts healthy and faster hair growth.

not only does the proteolytic enzyme help heal the scalp, but it also helps stimulate dormant hair follicles, promoting hair regrowth.

it also helps curb hair fall and controls hair shedding, ensuring that your hair remains thick and voluminous.

it has anti-inflammatory properties that help soothe your scalp of irritation and aggravation.

its antifungal and antiviral properties to treat dandruff and flaking.

aloe vera’s high content of protein, vitamins, and minerals help it nourish your follicles and hair efficiently.

the moisture content of aloe vera helps condition your hair, locking in nutrients and hydration

text:
3e post chiffré sur les "violences sexuelles et silence des victimes". sujet imaginé par @orfeas_gotronakis qui a mis en images le 5 novembre son propre vécu, comme d'autres le font par écrit.
.
aujourd'hui une nouvelle fausse idée : 
3. le viol, ça n’arrive pas souvent : faux
.
les chiffres sont tellement loin de la réalité, que l’association mémoire traumatique et victimologie sort en 2015 deux enquêtes : .
- "les	français	et les représentations	 sur	le	viol" avec ipsos sur un échantillon de 1 001 personnes (18 ans et +). 2 français sur 3 (65%) estiment que le nombre de viols ayant lieu chaque année en france ne dépasse pas le seuil des 50 000,  24% qu’il n’y en a qu’entre 1 000 et 10 000 par an !" ... la vérité ces 5 dernières années, c'est une moyenne  de 98 000 viols ou tentatives de viol par an... mais attention cela ne concernent que les 18-75 ans, qui ne tiennent donc pas compte des mineurs... alors que ce sont les premières victimes de violences sexuelles (81%). l'enquête « cadre de vie et sécurité 2010-2015 » de insee-ondrp estime à 124 000 filles et 30 000 garçons victimes de viols ou tentatives de viol chaque année, pour arriver à plus de 252 000 victimes...
.
.
- dans "impact des violences sexuelles de l'enfance à l'âge adulte", auprès de 1 214 victimes âgées de 15 et 72 ans, c'est 70% des personnes interrogées qui déclarent avoir subi plusieurs violences sexuelles, et 68% au moins un viol... 40% rapportent une situation d'inceste... 1 victime sur 2 est agressée avant 11 ans... et 1 sur 5 moins de 6 ans...
.
pour rendre concret ces chiffres : 
sur 800 000 naissances en 2015 (rapport de l'unaf) 13,9% risquent de subir au moins un viol...
.
#plo_society .
prochain post sur : "si la victime s’était défendue, ça ne serait pas arrivé : faux"
.
(sources : huffingtonpost.fr sur "violences sexuelles : 81% des victimes sont des mineurs..." ; ouest-france.fr "5 idées fausses sur les agressions sexuelles" , http://stopaudeni.com/rapport)
.
.
besoin d'aide : numéros d'écoute nationale, anonyme, gratuit pour les victimes :
- le 119 : maltraitance enfant/adolescent  7j/7j h24.

text:
20 years ago i quit architecture school after experiencing alienation & culture shock at @sciarc. i left the field but didn’t give up hope on reforms. i’m now part of reform efforts. i joined the @arch_lobby @archlobby.la, #losangeles chapter.

read our #manifesto 🌹

we are precarious workers. these are our demands:

1) enforce labor laws that prohibit unpaid internships, unpaid overtime; refuse unpaid competitions.

2) reject fees based on percentage of construction or hourly fees and instead calculate value based on the money we save our clients, or gain them.

3) stop peddling a product—buildings—and focus on the unique value architects help realize through spatial services.

4) enforce wage transparency across the discipline.

5) establish a union for architects, designers, academics and interns in architecture and design.

6) demystify the architect as solo creative genius; no honors for architects who don’t acknowledge their staff.

7) licensure upon completion of degree.

8) change professional architecture organizations to advocate for the living conditions of architects.

9) support research about professional labor rights in architecture.

10) implement democratic alternatives to the free market system of development.

the architecture lobby, inc. is an organization of architectural #workers advocating for the value of #architecture in the general public and for architectural work within the discipline. it believes that the work architects do—aesthetic, technical, social, organizational, environmental, administrative, fiduciary—needs structural change to be more rewarding and more socially relevant. as long as architecture tolerates abusive practices in the office and the construction site, it cannot insist on its role in and for the public good.

text:
i was frozen in my mind & heart about drawing illustrations for a children’s series i’m dreaming of. 
i’d tell myself, “you can only be an abstract artist.”
then my husband asked me a question that he already knew the answer to, “what was your dream when you went to college? what did you study & why?”
i immediately got tears in my eyes. i answered, “i was an art major/film minor.”
you see, i wanted to be an animator.
i wanted to work for disney or warner bros! 
except trauma started speaking to that dream. my choices took a devastating turn where i stepped into the sex industry & my life & dreams unraveled. 
years later, healing began. i began painting abstract & expressing my heart through paint. abstract felt safer to me. yet always afraid to draw. and if i tried, everything i did i saw as crap. junk. horrible art! 
so when bob asked me,
“what was your childhood dream when you went to college? what did you study & why?”
i answered in a new way...because of all of the healing i have received in the last couple of years, trauma didn’t get to answer the question this time. 
i am an artist. i can sketch. i can learn to illustrate. i am not afraid to try. 
and that longing and dream inside of me feels just as big as when i was younger & i believed i could do anything! 
what i’m learning...
it’s ok to renew a dream. 
trauma & abuse don’t get to dictate my life. 
it’s hard work healing from a lifetime of traumas. so never quit! 
art is hard work (and most all things you don’t know, are) & i will practice because it’s something i love deeply! 
happy new year friends! ❤️

text:
com 2018 chegando ao fim, gostaríamos de destacar algumas tendências do ano e compartilhar todas as maneiras pelas quais a comunidade do instagram chegou à plataforma para se expressar criativamente e se aproximar das pessoas - e coisas - que eles amam. 😍
.
compartilhar amor e bondade ainda é uma prioridade para a comunidade instagram: o heart love sticker de arata foi o adesivo giphy mais usado em stories, 💕enquanto heart eyes foi o filtro de face mais usado em histórias. no feed, o ❤ foi usado em comentários mais de 14 bilhões de vezes . o lugar mais feliz do mundo? disneyland tokyo, que viu o maior uso 🙂 na legenda!
.
o instagram é o lar de inúmeros interesses e comunidades; este ano, a asmr foi a principal tendência da comunidade de nichos do ano, com o corte de sabonete, o estalo de limos e o barbear de maquilhagem, continuando a aumentar a sua popularidade. 👾 o jogo fortnite também teve um crescimento explosivo, com a #fortnite sendo a hashtag que mais cresce no mundo. 📈 o domínio do k-pop nas mídias sociais é refletido pelo bts “army” sendo a principal comunidade de fãs na plataforma. 💃🏼 o maior desafio de dança viral do ano também nasceu no instagram, com #inmyfeelingschallenge.
.
por último, mas não menos importante, milhões de pessoas usaram o instagram para fazer suas vozes serem ouvidas em 2018. 🗣 as principais hashtags do ano foram #metoo (1,5 milhão), #timesup (597k), #marchforourlives (562k) , demonstrando que o instagram pode ser um poderoso plataforma para as pessoas falarem e trazerem luz para causas significativas.
.
fonte: instagram
.
para saber tudo sobre o mundo digital, acompanhe nosso blog e siga nossas redes sociais! 😉

in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
the sky is the limit ☁️
.
.
.
as the new year approaches, i always take time to reflect and think of ways i can ‘strike’ through my mind’s barriers – and strive to reach my full potential 🗒
.
.
.
it is so easy for our minds to create a vision of ‘perfection’ and exert mental energy trying to achieve this unrealistic goal.
. . 
the pressure we put ourselves in this way often leads to unproductive and negative thought cycles – in effect, becoming obstacles to achieving mental strength and achieving goals.
.
.
.
take a moment to consider what barrier you want to break through in the new year (or even before) and go for it! .
.
here are some tips that have helped me:
✅ write down what you want to achieve ✅check to see what negative beliefs are not serving you ✅ let go of your negative belief by replacing it with one of possibility ✨🙌🏻💪🏻
✅ identify at least one habit that will get you to your goal ✅ show up, take action, and be consistent.
.
.
.

text: i feel strongly enough about this news story to remind everyone that women’s rights also mean the right and the need to remind our daughters to be careful about what images they post of themselves and where they post them. beauty is often best when its subtle. as moms we must teach them to be cautious, to use the buddy system, to be aware of their surroundings, to avoid putting themselves in dangerous situations. lets make #metoo also #meownself meaning we think about protecting ourselves before bad things happen. #meownself please this holiday season encourage your daughters to be their own #meownself and take all precautionary measures they can.

text:
i really debated sharing this, but i also really wanted to leave this portion of my pain in 2018. i go through large spurts of growth and healing only to find myself still affected by my past every now and again. i know recovery isn’t linear, but it feels defeating sometimes. while i can’t guarantee this will stay in 2018, this is my effort to make it that way.
a few weeks ago my cousin shared with me that a friend of hers filed a no-contact order to keep an abusive ex out of her life, and she was met with support and encouragement from not only her friends and community, but the local pd as well. it made my heart so happy.
in the fall of 2015, i called the cops on my ex-husband one night. partly because he had just had one of his huge, out-of-proportion violent rages, and partly because he took to locking himself in his vehicle to drink and i couldn’t, no matter how much i was hurting, turn a blind eye with a good conscious.
however, when the cops arrived, i was the culprit. i was the reason behind my ex-husbands behavior. it didn’t matter how many months of emotional, mental, physical abuse and infidelity i put up with, i was the cause. it didn’t matter that he was a grown adult making his own decisions and choosing his behaviors. and i saw it, and heard it, when the cop taking my statement smiled and condescendingly said, “you know, if you had done something about this sooner, he wouldn’t be in this state tonight.”
if >i< had done something sooner? the months of pleading for him to get help? to see a therapist? the multiple times he got within centimeters of my face, threatening me if i told his superiors or did anything that might affect his employment? i was even afraid to drive myself to the hospital the night i tried to end my life for fear of retribution if word got out to his peers and superiors.
you mean every night he made the decision, as a full-grown 30-year-old man, to drink? to become emotionally manipulative and abusive?
and >i< should have done something about it sooner to positively affect him? i, as many women in my culture growing up in the valley, put the entire weight of my marriage on my shoulders. i blamed myself for every failing.
name: Rebecca Izaguirre

i really debated sharing this, but i also really wanted to leave this poion of my pain in 2018. i go through large spus of growth and healing only to find myself still affected by my past every now and again. i know recovery isn’t linear, but it feels defeating sometimes. while i can’t guarantee this will stay in 2018, this is my effo to make it that way.
a few weeks ago my cousin shared with me that a friend of hers filed a no-contact order to keep an abusive ex out of her life, and she was met with suppo and encouragement from not only her friends and community, but the local pd as well. it made my hea so happy.
in the fall of 2015, i called the cops on my ex-husband one night. paly because he had just had one of his huge, out-of-propoion violent rages, and paly because he took to locking himself in his vehicle to drink and i couldn’t, no matter how much i was huing, turn a blind eye with a good conscious.
however, when the cops arrived, i was the culprit. i was the reason behind my ex-husbands behavior. it didn’t matter how many months of emotional, mental, physical abuse and infidelity i put up with, i was the cause. it didn’t matter that he was a grown adult making his own decisions and choosing his behaviors. and i saw it, and heard it, when the cop taking my statement smiled and condescendingly said, “you know, if you had done something about this sooner, he wouldn’t be in this state tonight.”
if >i< had done something sooner? the months of pleading for him to get help? to see a therapist? the multiple times he got within centimeters of my face, threatening me if i told his superiors or did anything that might affect his employment? i was even afraid to drive myself to the hospital the night i tried to end my life for fear of retribution if word got out to his peers and superiors.
you mean every night he made the decision, as a full-grown 30-year-old man, to drink? to become emotionally manipulative and abusive?
and >i< should have done something about it sooner to positively affect him? i, as many women in my culture growing up in the valley, put the entire weight of my marriage on my shoulders. i blamed myself for every failing.

text:
i’ve spent a lot of today processing the incredible experience i had yesterday, supporting this amazing cause. this isn’t meant to be a boastful post at all about how i spent my christmas.. although i went excitedly along to teach yoga, there was just a bit of that in the end, and my learnings were not the shape making on the mat in the way that i envisaged. i was touched by the many people i came into contact with and really blown away that 99% of the residents in the centre i volunteered in were men. at the time i was really shocked by this, but thinking about it more i guess it’s no surprise in some ways. more and more statistics show that male suicide is on the rise... and although #metoo has been so important and totally can’t be ignored, the anger around this seems to have somehow overshadowed the many other good people out there, men and women alike. i came away feeling like some important healing and deeper bridge building still needs to happen between men and women. it seems that so much is still misunderstood about the needs and vulnerabilities of both sexes and how we can now truly meet each other on a more human level and not based on what is somehow expected by society or conditioning. it really was food for thought for me, and such an eye opening experience. 
today i’m feeling grateful not just for the roof over my head, and the many blessings in my life but the connections i have with both the men  and women, all those close, and the amazing healers, yoga teachers, therapists, and other amazing creatives of all kinds who step out in the world and are trying to help build these bridges, supporting a world where we can all just meet each other, and live a life filled with wholeness and love and really be met as we are. feels like something i want to carry with me, as i leave this year and step into a new one. not just in terms of what i offer out to others in my creativity but also how open hearted i want to be and really be grateful for each day and grab life, as well as really connect and love  the people i’m fortunate enough to share my life with ❤️🙏🏼❤️

text:
why me, was a question that i often asked myself growing up as a hopeless sexually abused child.

i didn’t have a relationship with the lord then, and yet even now as a believer i still ask, why me. 
but this time it’s different.

i no longer ask the lord why me with a bitter, angry, sad, frustrated, heart, but with a heart of humility that seeks to know how god wants to use me and my sexual abuse past to help point others to christ and build his kingdom.

realizing and embracing the fact that the evil of sexual abuse that happened to me was all apart of god’s sovereign plan, i no longer dwell on my suffering, sorrow, and self-pity.

instead i choose to hope in and trust god, even if i don’t fully understand his plan or purpose, because his ways are higher than mine and his thoughts are higher than mine,isaiah 55:8-9.

i serve a faithful, loving, sovereign lord...““and we know that god causes all things to work together for good to those who love god, to those who are called according to his purpose.” romans‬ ‭8:28‬

text:
на мой взгляд лучший, неожиданный ночной визит на кухню к холодильнику. думаю даже лучший на все времена.

мерилин монро после громкого, тяжелого и скандального бракоразводного процесса ушла от легенды бейсбола итальянца ди маджо, который регулярно покалачивал ее, ставил синяки, и воспитывал в сицилийском стиле. немного погрустив, поплакав, "дива америки" переехала залечивать свои душевные, и не только душевные раны к своему другу, приятелю, и просто к хорошему парню, "американскому идолу" френку синатре. отношение у них были вполне дружеские, и ровные, без всяких #metoo.

но, многие искры воспламеняющие, выжигающие, становящиеся страшным пожаром, часто высекаются случайно. все произошло у холодильника, ночью. как когда-то у чудесного несгораемого шкафа. 
однажды ночью, которая уже становилась утром, голодный синатра вошел на кухню и неожиданно у холодильника увидел абсолютно голую и голодную мэрилин. холодильник был открыт, секс-идол монро нагнулась к нижним секциям и выбирала себе на завтрак фрукт. она не могла решить апельсин или грейпфрут лучше на завтрак. 
о, фрэнки, я думала, ты еще спишь... это были ее последние слова, перед тем как обезумевший фрэнки за нее выбрал, что будет лучше на завтрак.

одним словом, теперь идя ночью за едой к холодильнику, будь готов к любым сюрпризам.
name: Rovshan Kerimov
tweet_full:
на мой взгляд лучший, неожиданный ночной визит на кухню к холодильнику. думаю даже лучший на все времена.

мерилин монро после громкого, тяжелого и скандального бракоразводного процесса ушла от легенды бейсбола итальянца ди маджо, который регулярно покалачивал ее, ставил синяки, и воспитывал в сицилийском стиле. немного погрустив, поплакав, "дива америки" переехала залечивать свои душевные, и не только душевные раны к своему другу, приятелю, и просто к хорошему парню, "американскому идолу" френку синатре. отношение у них были вполне дружеские, и ровные, без всяких #metoo.

но, многие искры воспламеняющие, выжигающие, становящиеся страшным пожаром, часто высекаются случайно. все произошло у холодильника, ночью. как когда-то у чудесного несгораемого шкафа. 
однажды ночью, которая уже становилась утром, голодный синатра вошел на кухню и неожиданно у холодильника увидел абсолютно голую и голодную мэрилин. холодильник был открыт, секс-идол монро нагнулась к нижним секциям и выбирала себе на завтрак фрукт. она не могла решить апельсин или грейпфрут лучше на завтрак. 
о, фрэнки, я думала, ты еще спишь... это были ее последние слова, перед тем как обезумевший фрэнки за нее выбрал, что будет лучше на завтрак.

одним словом, теперь идя ночью за едой к холодильнику, будь готов к любым сюрпризам.

вряд ли найдутся люди, которые не слышали о футболе⚽️, баскетболе🏀 или бейсболе⚾️. эти виды спорта распространены по всему миру. однако локальные спортивные мероприятия заслуживают вашего внимания ничуть не меньше. скажем сразу, что творческий💡 подход людей к спорту не оставит вас равнодушными. здесь представлены соревнования на любой вкус: от простых интерпретаций популярных видов спорта до совершенно уникальных игр, оригинальность которых доходит до абсурда.
⠀
💥итак, перед вами 25 самых необычных видов спорта в мире!💥
⠀
❌куперсхилдская сырная гонка❌⠀
ежегодно на живописных котсуолдских холмах проводится игра, в которой толпа смельчаков бежит вниз по склону холма, в погоне за головкой двойного глостерского сыра. люди со всех концов света съезжаются к холму купера, чтобы посмотреть и даже принять участие в этом опасном, но очень веселом состязании.
⠀
❌хёрлинг❌⠀
сможете ли вы представить себе сочетание футбола, бейсбола и хоккея? а в ирландии уже существует игра под названием хёрлинг, которая идеально подходит под это описание. экипировка игрока-хёрлера состоит из футбольной формы, защитного шлема и деревянной клюшки. цель этой игры состоит в том, чтобы заработать как можно больше очков, забивая мячи в ворота соперника.
⠀

ежегодно на живописных котсуолдских холмах проводится игра, в которой толпа смельчаков бежит вниз по склону холма, в погоне за головкой двойного глостерского сыра. люди со всех концов света съезжаются к холму купера, чтобы посмотреть и даже принять участие в этом опасном, но очень веселом состязании.
⠀
❌хёрлинг❌⠀
сможете ли вы представить себе сочетание футбола, бейсбола и хоккея? а в ирландии уже существует игра под названием хёрлинг, которая идеально подходит под это описание. экипировка игрока-хёрлера состоит из футбольной формы, защитного шлема и деревянной клюшки. цель этой игры состоит в том, чтобы заработать как можно больше очков, забивая мячи в ворота соперника.
⠀
📌продолжение в нашей группе vk.com/mgfso (ссылка в описании профиля).
⠀

text:
to the girl from the city,

i'm reena. i'm 16 years old and i too have the same dreams and aspirations just like you. but i know being a girl is not easy. people judge you everyday, everytime. being uneducated, living in an unknown village from bengal i don't know how to write letters or read the news. my neighbor has a radio which is turned on throughout the day. i've heard a lot of stories about the women being raped in the clubs. the skirts, the short dresses always become the victims. living in a well educated society you people started a #metoo movement recently exposing the wrongs done to you.
-
let me tell you. i also have a story to share. we don't have any social media or any mode of communicating the world. we don't get the opportunity to share our stories instead we need to hide them. so let me speak out. let me tell you its not only the skirts that become the victims of rape but the burkhas and salwar kameez all fall in the list. -
shhh... don't tell this to anyone. okay? or else my abba will lock me up in a room again. this should remain only between you and me. believe me the situation of the girls living in a village are lot more difficult. last tuesday, my seven year old sister was touched inappropriately. last week, my elder sister was physically assaulted. and last night, me. my drunkard dad, came up to me. i was sleeping cosily in my bed. i could suddenly feel the chills as i could feel someone's fingers slowly moving over my private part. i woke up late in the night. suddenly. all i found was my dad. i couldn't speak just because he put a cloth in my mouth, tied my hands. i was screaming. i could find my amma's vocie outside the room. he pulled my pants, slowly moving his nasty tongue over my vagina. and then i could feel the piercing. ohhh...god. the blood oozed out. i begged, i prayed. yet he didn't listen. he continued to use his manly power and desires until he was done. i was left all alone in my room throughout the night. next morning, when i told my maa what happened last night, she kept silent. all she said was 'tum ladki ho. ye yoh hoti hi rahegi. take some pills.' i went up to my dad.

text:
cuando asia dijo que ella era la víctima todos le creyeron. primero lo negó todo, luego no le quedó otra salida que confesar la verdad, pero dijo que ella había sido la víctima. 
en el caso de abuso sexual contra asia argento.

pregunta: por qué asia, que fue una de las que impulsó la campaña #metoo luego de que estallara la bomba de abusos por parte de harvey weinstein, no dijo nada de esto? por qué lo negó todo la primera vez? por qué cambio la versión luego de que se demostrará que realmente había tenido intimidad con jimmy bennett (en ese momento un menor de 17 años)?. esto me recuerda que escuché a profesionales decir en el caso de thelma fardin y juan darthes que el abusador siempre le echa la culpa a la víctima. me pregunto si está psicología también aplica para las mujeres o solo para actores famosos hombres que intentan defenderse en cámara (no defiendo ni apoyo a darthes). escuché a una feminista decir: "si la mujer realmente fue víctima no tiene nada de que temer" , otra interrogante en el caso de asia que le pagó a su supuesto "abusador" para que él caso no llegara a tribunales. 
por qué crees que este caso quedó en el olvido?

#feminista #metoo #antifeminismo #antiprogre #salvemoslas2vidas #miracomonosponemos

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

our favorite excerpt: "as women, we are warned that life in the medical field will be more difficult than life for our male colleagues. this can manifest as anything from being repeatedly mistaken for the nurse to wage inequality. however the difference that may wear the most is the constant sexual harassment."
📖
thank you so much to dr. chernoby for starting this difficult conversation.

text:
habari gani? umoja! to strive for and maintain unity in the family, community, nation and race.
unity doesn't mean blind loyalty. in contrast, umoja challenges us to hold one another accountable, to see ourselves in our brothers and sisters, and ultimately to understand that our fates are intertwined.
umoja fully recognizes intersectionality and says that the individual cannot be free unless the group is free. i say this in the wake of the #metoo moment this year. how many black women remained silent to protect black men who were their abusers? i honor and uplift all the black women who did speak up. i honor and uplift the black woman, tarana burke, who started the #metoo movement because sexual violence against black women is under-reported and overlooked. umoja means we cannot deal with just one issue - racism or sexism or whatever else. umoja requires an "and".
#umoja #kwanzaa #happykwanzaa #intersectionality #blackwomen #unity

text:
parce que le sexisme est encore présent partout et en particulier dans la publicité. 
pourquoi cette publicité pour l'épilation est sexiste ? -elle objectifie (rend objet) la femme en ne représentant qu'une partie de son corps (reste du corps découpé et surtout tête absente)
-cette publicité est une injonction à l'épilation pour les femmes (déjà ultra présente dans la société), pas de présence d'homme pour contre-balancer le dictat. -"offrez-lui la douceur": la femme doit-elle forcément modifier son corps, s'imposer une pratique coûteuse, douleureuse et chronophage pour être belle et plaire aux hommes ? c'est ce que l'on comprend ici. c'est une véritable injonction pour les femmes à se plier aux dictats de beauté au nom du "plaisir" masculin. 
nous militons pour que les femmes soient tout simplement libres de décider si oui ou non elles veulent s'épiler et que celles qui refusent soient acceptées et surtout pas jugées puisque oui les femmes ont des poils et peuvent choisir de les garder ou non.

text:
happy boxing day #frotribe. .
.
i'm sure we're all busy packing on the holiday calories. i know i am.. 😁😁😁
.
.

so due to the very very dry and cold weather, i had to make aloe vera juice to be used as my daily hair spritz. all i added to it was a few drops of my hair growth elixir.  so perfect! 🤗🤗. .
.

aloe vera is very very effective in maintaining a moisturized hair and preventing dryness and itchy scalp. .
.
so picture 1 is the freshly cut aloe vera leaves. make sure to use the big mature and juicy ones. .
.
picture 2 is the extracted gel which i got by using a sharp knife to gently slice off the green parts of the leave. the gel is housed in the center of the leaves. .
.
picture 3 is the final product which is the aloe vera juice. i got this by blending the extracted gel with about a cup of water which i then sieved using a cheese cloth to extract the pulp. .
voila!  the aloe vera juice is ready. .
simple right? .
i transferred it to my spray bottle and added a few drops of @fro_guard hair growth elixir. .
.
.
my next post will be on the benefits of aloe vera to the hair. .
.
who else loves using aloe vera? 🙋
.
.

text:
artemisia gentileschi “self-portait as saint catherine of alexandria”, 1615-17, national gallery london.

this wonderful self-portrait by one of the few recognised female painters of the late renaissance or perhaps baroque era is on special display after its acquisition last year. surprisingly, it’s only the 20th painting by a female artist in the national galleries collection. there’s a good personal back story to help explain this psychologically interesting painting. well worth a visit. #metoo

text:
we are pleased to announce our first national essay writing competition, that is a small step in our endeavour to create social awareness and a sense of social responsibility in the youth citizens of our country.
the above stated competition will be adjudged by jury consisting of law faculty from 5 prestigious law colleges. 
the topics for the competition are:
*failure of legal machinery & emergence of #metoo moment *transformative constitutionalism and subrimala judgement
*sustainable development in india & around the world.

the last date of submission of essays is 31st of january, and the registration shall be completed by 20th january.

for registration the candidates need to fill the googleform provided in the given link:
https://goo.gl/forms/th7knjakch6s9jnj2 
the registration fee is rs 250 
winning prize is rs 5100 along with rs 2100 for runner-up, every participant will be advanced an e-certificate under the banner of "social-curator"
for any further queries contact at:
ph:9780361242, 7973767217
email:socialcurator4@gmail.com

text:
the #metoo movement has caused men on wall street and high level executives to walk on eggshell around women and are incorporating the "pence effect" where he avoids dining alone with a women other than his wife.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i read an article on this on bloomberg. men are scared. they don't know how to behave around women. what is allowed and what isn't. those poor men, so confused (insert full sarcasm here). ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this article is an insult to men. most men know exactly how to behave around women. they know how to be respectful, how not to slap her bum at work or insinuate intercourse during a business dinner. it's an insult to good men like my husband, and so many others. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
women in high level positions are now being forced to figure out how to deal with this situation. wall street might become an even bigger boys club is what the article says. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i don't believe it. i believe in women. we are a smart bunch. and i believe that the bad apples are about to be weeded out. you see, if a man doesn't know what is right when it comes being around women. he isn't fit to be in a high level position or to run a company. he has lost his ethics and values. if he can't treat female business partners with respect, he has no place in that company.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
